Has to be sarcasm.<p>People who actually believe that wouldn&#x27;t say &quot;politicians&quot;, they&#x27;d use some other euphemism, because they believe in some abstract trustworthy organization that&#x27;s always being hampered by those damn politicians.<p>Statists love their euphemisms:
“investment” instead of “government spending”
“shared sacrifices” instead of &quot;wealth redistribution&quot;
&quot;government officials&quot; instead of &quot;un-elected bureaucrat&quot;
and lastly,
&quot;public sector&quot; instead of &quot;The State&quot;.
